                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Coolidge</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-04-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Coolidge reports that the new arrangement for the payment of the Chinese
                    indemnity will probably be signed very soon. Payments of arrears will be made
                    directly to each government within fifteen days after signature by telegraphic
                    transfer. Recommends adoption of such transfers on New York in American dollars.
                    Requests instruction.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
